<h1>Word Spacing</h1>
<div id="intro" class="instructions">
Use CSS to replicate the pictured eye chart. To accomplish this: 
<ol>
	<li>Adjust size, text-alignment and word-spacing on each of the divs (topLine, secondLine, thirdLine, etc) to adjust the display of letters in that span</li>
	<li>Adjust the padding and margins of the eye chart div to roughly match the dimensions of the eye-chart and the placement of text on the chart.</li>
	<li>Adjust the margins of each div within the chart to fine-tune the appearance of rows of text. </li>
	<li>If you replicate the appearance of the letters on the chart, and want to add the green and red lines, try adding a bottom border to the appropriate div and setting it to a very large size</li>
	<li>If you finish all this, try to find a google font that approximates the font shown in the chart, add it to this document, and apply it to the eyeChart div.</li>
</div>
